Ouba has now left Opportunity Disability Care Center

After completing school at Opportunity International Development Services in Burundi, Ouba found work as a waiter. Once he began earning money, Opportunity International Burundi’s savings group leader taught him how to save. As a member of a savings group, he learned how to handle money responsibly and save for the future. To make his end of year one payment, he had to prepare the capital sum in US dollars and convert them to Burundi francs. He planned well and succeeded in making his payment on time.

Once Ouba was able to trust the savings groups with his money, then he started to invest in a local poultry farm.
